.TH AI-PLAYBOOK-SKILL 1 "" "ai-playbook" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
ai\-playbook\-skill \- Print or install the playbook\-authoring skill
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBai\-playbook\fR skill <show|install> [\-\-to <dir>] [\-\-force]
.SH DESCRIPTION
skill ships the embedded playbook\-authoring SKILL (the harness\-agnostic
authoring guide derived from docs/specifications/playbook\-authoring.md:
schema quick\-reference, the nine\-rule quality rubric, a worked example,
and the validate iteration loop).
.PP
skill show
    Print the SKILL markdown to stdout (pipe it anywhere).
.PP
skill install [\-\-to <dir>] [\-\-force]
    Write the SKILL to <dir>/playbook\-authoring/SKILL.md, creating
    directories as needed. Default <dir>: ~/.claude/skills (the Claude
    Code personal skills directory). An existing file is never
    overwritten without \-\-force. Prints the installed path on success.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-to\fR \fI<dir>\fR
install under this skills directory instead of ~/.claude/skills (install)
.TP
\fB\-\-force\fR
overwrite an already\-installed SKILL.md (install)
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
ai\-playbook skill show
.fi
.PP
.nf
ai\-playbook skill install
.fi
.PP
.nf
ai\-playbook skill install \-\-to ./.claude/skills \-\-force
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
\fBai\-playbook\fR(1)
